# Neovim Configuration

A modern Neovim setup focused on productivity and development workflow. Built with Lua and managed by lazy.nvim.

## Overview

This configuration transforms Neovim into a powerful IDE-like editor with LSP support, fuzzy finding, git integration, and modern editing features. Includes Zed-inspired keybindings for familiar workflows.

## Features

### Core
- **Plugin Manager**: lazy.nvim for fast, lazy-loaded plugins
- **Leader Key**: Space for intuitive command access
- **Persistent Undo**: Unlimited undo history via undotree
- **Smart Search**: Case-insensitive with smart case detection

### LSP & Completion
- **Language Server Protocol**: Full LSP integration with diagnostics
- **Completions**: blink.cmp and nvim-cmp for intelligent autocompletion
- **Inline Diagnostics**: Real-time error feedback
- **Fidget**: LSP progress notifications

### Navigation & Editing
- **Telescope**: Fuzzy finder for files, buffers, and grep
- **Harpoon**: Quick file switching for frequently used files
- **Flash**: Lightning-fast cursor movement
- **Oil**: File explorer with buffer-like editing
- **UFO**: Advanced code folding

### Code Intelligence
- **Treesitter**: Advanced syntax highlighting and parsing
- **Conform**: Code formatting
- **Autotag/Autopairs**: Smart bracket and tag handling
- **Surround**: Easy manipulation of surrounding characters
- **Inc-rename**: Preview symbol renaming across files

### TypeScript/JavaScript
- **TS Error Translator**: Human-readable TypeScript errors
- **Two-slash**: Type annotations support
- **TS Addons**: Enhanced TypeScript tooling

### Git Integration
- **Gitsigns**: Git status indicators in the gutter
- **Lazygit**: Full git UI via terminal integration

### UI & Visual
- **Colorschemes**: Monokai and Sonokai themes
- **Which-key**: Command palette and keybinding hints
- **Indent Blankline**: Visual indent guides
- **Highlight Colors**: Preview color codes inline
- **Render Markdown**: Beautiful markdown rendering
- **Trouble**: Pretty diagnostics and quickfix list

### Utilities
- **Todo Comments**: Highlight and search TODO/FIXME comments
- **Mini.nvim**: Collection of small useful utilities

## Structure

```
~/.config/nvim/
├── init.lua              # Core settings and keymaps
├── lua/
│   ├── config/
│   │   └── lazy.lua      # Plugin manager bootstrap
│   └── plugins/          # Individual plugin configs
└── lazy-lock.json        # Locked plugin versions
```

## Key Settings

- **Line Numbers**: Relative with absolute current line
- **Tabs**: 4 spaces, smart indentation
- **Text Width**: 80 columns with visual indicator
- **Scrolloff**: 10 lines above/below cursor
- **Terminal**: True color support, rounded borders

## Notable Keybindings

| Key | Action | Notes |
|-----|--------|-------|
| `Space` | Leader key | Primary command prefix |
| `Space w` | Save buffer | Quick write |
| `Space g g` | Lazygit | Git interface |
| `Alt-t` | Toggle terminal | Quick terminal access |
| `Space s r/l/d/u` | Split window | Directional splits |
| `Space t n/p` | Next/prev diagnostic | Zed-style navigation |
| `] d / [ d` | Next/prev diagnostic | Vim-style navigation |
| `g h` | Show diagnostic | Hover diagnostics |
| `Ctrl-h/j/k/l` | Navigate splits | Vim window movement |

## Requirements

- Neovim nightly (or >= 0.10)
- Nerd Font (for icons)
- lazygit (for git integration)
- Language servers for LSP features
- Formatters for conform.nvim

## Notes

- Change operations (`c`, `C`) redirected to black hole register to preserve yanks
- Clipboard integrated with system clipboard (`unnamedplus`)
- Persistent undo stored in `.undodir`
- Keybindings inspired by both Vim traditions and modern editors like Zed

